{"type":"message","id":"eae4fc7e","parentId":"090de9a4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:44:09.265Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1m2okmm9hlri_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5436\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2662\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[master 01450a4] pulse: 2026-03-23 184343\n 7 files changed, 358 insertions(+), 125 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 184343.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 184343.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 183035.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 184343 - The TIC experiment requires analyzing existing pulse logs (`logs/pulse_*.md`) to classify invariant vs variant patterns. I need to first examine the actual structure and content of recent pulse logs to design an effective classifier.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"ember-summit","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5436\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2662\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[master 01450a4] pulse: 2026-03-23 184343\n 7 files changed, 358 insertions(+), 125 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 184343.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 184343.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 183035.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 184343 - The TIC experiment requires analyzing existing pulse logs (`logs/pulse_*.md`) to classify invariant vs variant patterns. I need to first examine the actual structure and content of recent pulse logs to design an effective classifier.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774305849262}}
{"type":"message","id":"68a96fe4","parentId":"eae4fc7e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:44:09.269Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1m2okmm9hlri_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-23 183035\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nThe current goal is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression):\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Look at the recent pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier that can identify invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Implement the experiment\r\n\r\nLet me first check what's in the logs directory and recent pulse files to understand the format.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier on pulse logs to identify invariant vs variant content. I need to examine recent pulse files to understand their structure before building the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs for temporal invariants, then run it on recent pulses to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [string]$OutputFile = \"research/TIC_RESULTS.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Collect pulse files sorted by date\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object Name | Select-Object -Last 20\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 2) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Insufficient pulse files (need at least 2, found $($pulseFiles.Count))\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Analyzing $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse files...\"\r\n\r\n# Extract content patterns from each pulse\r\nfunction Get-PulsePatterns {\r\n    param([string]$FilePath)\r\n    \r\n    $content = Get-Content $FilePath -Raw\r\n    \r\n    # Extract key patterns: goals, insights, file references, action items\r\n    $patterns = @{\r\n        Goals = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?m)^##?\\s+(Goal|Active|Completed|Pending)[\\s:]') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n        Files = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?:\\.\\./|\\./)?[\\w/]+(?:\\.\\w+)?') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value } | Select-Object -Unique\r\n        Actions = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?m)^- \\[ \\] (.+)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value }\r\n        Timestamps = [regex]::Matches($content, '\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}|\\d{2}:\\d{2}:\\d{2}') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n        Insights = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?i)(?:insight|key finding|hypothesis): (.+)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $patterns\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Build pattern database across all pulses\r\n$allPatterns = @{\r\n    PersistentGoals = @{}\r\n    VariantGoals = @{}\r\n    PersistentFiles = @{}\r\n    VariantFiles = @{}\r\n    PersistentActions = @()\r\n    VariantActions = @()\r\n}\r\n\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $patterns = Get-PulsePatterns $file.FullName\r\n    $allPatterns.PersistentGoals[$file.Name] = $patterns.Goals\r\n    $allPatterns.PersistentFiles[$file.Name] = $patterns.Files\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Identify invariants (patterns appearing in >70% of pulses)\r\n$goalCounts = @{}\r\n$fileCounts = @{}\r\n\r\nforeach ($goals in $allPatterns.PersistentGoals.Values) {\r\n    foreach ($g in $goals) {\r\n        $goalCounts[$g] = ($goalCounts[$g] ?? 0) + 1\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nforeach ($files in $allPatterns.PersistentFiles.Values) {\r\n    foreach ($f in $files) {\r\n        if ($f -match '\\.\\./') { continue }  # Skip relative paths\r\n        $fileCounts[$f] = ($fileCounts[$f] ?? 0) + 1\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$threshold = [math]::Ceiling($pulseFiles.Count * 0.7)\r\n$invariants = @{\r\n    Goals = $goalCounts.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value -ge $threshold } | ForEach-Object { $_.Key }\r\n    Files = $fileCounts.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value -ge $threshold } | ForEach-Object { $_.Key }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate metrics\r\n$totalPatterns = $goalCounts.Count + $fileCounts.Count\r\n$invariantCount = $invariants.Goals.Count + $invariants.Files.Count\r\n$classificationRate = if ($totalPatterns -gt 0) { ($invariantCount / $totalPatterns) * 100 } else { 0 }\r\n\r\n# Predict next pulse from invariants (simple forward reference)\r\n$lastPulse = Get-PulsePatterns ($pulseFiles | Select-Object -Last 1).FullName\r\n$predictedActions = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($invGoal in $invariants.Goals) {\r\n    if ($lastPulse.Goals -notcontains $invGoal) {\r\n        $predictedActions += \"Carry forward: $invGoal\"\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$predictionAccuracy = $predictedActions.Count / [math]::Max(1, $allPatterns.PersistentGoals.Count)\r\n\r\n# Generate results\r\n$results = @\"\r\n# TIC Experiment Results\r\n\r\n**Date:** $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\r\n**Pulse files analyzed:** $($pulseFiles.Count)\r\n**Invariant threshold:** $threshold of $($pulseFiles.Count) ($($\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 18:31:00\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774305849265}}
