{"type":"message","id":"5cea1890","parentId":"6aa73dce","timestamp":"2026-03-23T22:44:16.887Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lwiinupxwoh5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 184343\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 (Architecture cross-analysis) are complete\r\n2. Gap-Decay synthesis is done\r\n3. LLM-Augmented Pulse is working\r\n4. Pending items include:\r\n   - Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n   - Define significance scoring\r\n   - Tune λ empirically\r\n   - Wire to TemporalAttention backend\r\n   - Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe key insight is \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The next action should be implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment.\r\n\r\nLooking at the recent pulse log mentioned: `pulse_2026-03-23 183035.md`\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step would be to:\r\n1. Implement a TIC classifier on the pulse logs\r\n2. Or write the PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n3. Or define significance scoring\r\n\r\nGiven the current priorities around the TIC experiment, I should implement the TIC classifier on the existing pulse logs. Let me check what's available.\r\n\r\nActually, looking more carefully at the goals:\r\n- \"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\" is clearly marked as the priority\r\n- It involves implementing a TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nLet me implement the TIC experiment. I need to:\r\n1. Read existing pulse logs\r\n2. Implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns\r\n3. Predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nA concrete action would be to create a TIC classifier script or document that outlines the implementation.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script for the TIC experiment, or better yet, a PowerShell wrapper since that's one of the pending items and aligns with the need to process the pulse logs.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending items, the PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI is listed, and the TIC experiment needs to process pulse logs. \r\n\r\nI should start by examining the existing pulse logs to understand their structure. This will help me design an effective classifier that can identify invariant and variant patterns within the data. By analyzing the logs first, I can create a more targeted and accurate implementation for the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires analyzing existing pulse logs (`logs/pulse_*.md`) to classify invariant vs variant patterns. I need to first examine the actual structure and content of recent pulse logs to design an effective classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation by first inspecting existing pulse logs and then building the invariance detection script.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n\r\n## Experiment Overview\r\nTests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n```python\r\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\nAnalyzes pulse logs to detect invariant patterns and predict next content.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\r\n\r\nPULSE_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef parse_pulse_filename(filename):\r\n    match = PULSE_PATTERN.match(filename.name)\r\n    if match:\r\n        date_str, time_str = match.groups()\r\n        dt = datetime.strptime(f\"{date_str}_{time_str}\", \"%Y-%m-%d_%H%M%S\")\r\n        return dt\r\n    return None\r\n\r\ndef load_pulses():\r\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse logs sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for f in sorted(PULSE_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=lambda x: x.name):\r\n        dt = parse_pulse_filename(f)\r\n        if dt:\r\n            content = f.read_text()\r\n            pulses.append({\"dt\": dt, \"path\": f, \"content\": content})\r\n    return sorted(pulses, key=lambda x: x[\"dt\"])\r\n\r\ndef extract_features(pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract invariant vs variant features from a pulse.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse[\"content\"]\r\n    features = {\r\n        \"has_goal_section\": bool(re.search(r\"## (Goals|Active|Completed)\", content)),\r\n        \"has_mutation\": bool(re.search(r\"### MUTATION\", content)),\r\n        \"has_observation\": bool(re.search(r\"### OBSERVATION\", content)),\r\n        \"has_action\": bool(re.search(r\"### ACTION\", content)),\r\n        \"line_count\": len(content.split(\"\\n\")),\r\n        \"section_count\": len(re.findall(r\"^## \", content, re.MULTILINE)),\r\n        \"subsection_count\": len(re.findall(r\"^### \", content, re.MULTILINE)),\r\n        \"has_timestamp\": \"2026\" in content,\r\n        \"has_file_refs\": bool(re.search(r\"`[a-zA-Z0-9_/.-]+`\", content)),\r\n    }\r\n    return features\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariants(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Detect invariant features across pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    all_features = [extract_features(p) for p in pulses]\r\n    \r\n    # Features that remain constant = invariants\r\n    invariants = []\r\n    variants = []\r\n    \r\n    for feature_name in all_features[0].keys():\r\n        values = [f[feature_name] for f in all_features]\r\n        if len(set(values)) == 1:\r\n            invariants.append(feature_name)\r\n        else:\r\n            variants.append((feature_name, Counter(values)))\r\n    \r\n    return {\"invariants\": invariants, \"variants\": variants}\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(pulses, n_train=5):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 18:44:08\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774305856884}}
